Under the circumstances you state in your kind letter received this morning, I think I shall do well to accept the offer of M. Weber.<note></note> Therefore let me hereby empower you to accept that gentleman's proposal, on my Johann Jakob Weber (1803-80), another Leipzig publisher, who printed several Dickens texts in translation, among them <hi rend="italic">Die Pickwickier</hi> (1837).behalf. And pray let me thank you at the same time, cordially, for the trouble and interest you have taken in the business.
